column4:
The candidate report has several discrepancies when compared to the reference report. The candidate report fails to mention the subtle scoliosis concavity on the right side, the advanced degenerative spinal changes, and the spina bifida at S1. It also incorrectly states that there is no scoliosis and misassesses the severity of the degenerative changes. 

[Clinically Significant Errors]:
(a) False report of a finding in the candidate: 1. No scoliosis;
(b) Missing a finding present in the reference: 3. Subtle scoliosis concavity right side; Advanced degenerative spinal changes; Spina bifida S1;
(d) Misassessment of the severity of a finding: 1. Mild degenerative changes instead of advanced degenerative spinal changes;

[Clinically Insignificant Errors]:
None.

[Matched Findings]:
3. Normal bone density; No fractures or lesions; No vertebral body height loss.
